     <h2><font color="#000080"><!-- 2004-09-02 -->
	 <a href="http://www.ss.astro.umd.edu/IAU/csbn/" 
                     title="external link">
	 The Final Page
	 </a></font>
     </h2>
    

	<p>
    <div style="clear:both;"></div>From M.Sc in IT classmate Geoffrey Canham comes this link:<blockquote>Some good advice seen in New Scientist magazine this week:&nbsp; Go to <a href="http://www.ss.astro.umd.edu/IAU/csbn/">http://www.ss.astro.umd.edu/IAU/csbn/</a>, scroll to the bottom of the page and click on the 'The Real World' link.</blockquote>I would love to say that is what I have been doing and that it accounts for my blog-block, but that isn't it.&nbsp; This as good a start as any for unblocking, though.&nbsp; Enjoy.<hr /><small>I have some pent up blogging to unleash, although I am doing the right thing by focusing on my now-approved M.Sc dissertation topic.&nbsp; Meanwhile, another dissertation-weary classmate remarked that "The Final Page" is what he would like to find as he struggles with literature searching on the internet.</small><div style="clear:both; padding-bottom:0.25em"></div>
    </p>
	<span class="byline">posted by orcmid 
       at <a href="http://orcmid.com/blog/2005/03/final-page.asp">3/02/2005 08:17:00 PM</a></span>
	  
         <!-- 2004-05-10 -->
